Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the 101st National Convention of the American Legion in Indianapolis, Indiana. He expressed his gratitude for the service and sacrifice of veterans and highlighted the administration's efforts to support them. Pence mentioned that the American Legion is the largest veterans organization in America and praised its work in caring for veterans and supporting their families. He also discussed the administration's initiatives to rebuild the military, improve the VA, and create job opportunities for veterans. Pence emphasized the importance of upholding the ideals of freedom and defending against socialism. He concluded by honoring the fallen soldiers and expressing gratitude for their service.